g.type !== 'color'\">\n\t\t<input type=\"range\" inline title=\"Opacity\" name=\"overlayOpacity\" min=\"0\" max=\"1\" step=\"0.1\" value=\"0.8\" condition=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\">\n\t</mbr-parameters>\n\n\t<div class=\"mbr-fallback-image disabled\" mbr-if=\"bg.type == 'video'\"></div>\n\t<div class=\"mbr-overlay\" mbr-if=\"overlay && bg.type !== 'color'\" opacity=\"{{overlayOpacity}}\" bg-color=\"{{overlayColor}}\"></div>\n\n\t<div mbr-class=\"{'container': !fullWidth, 'container-fluid': fullWidth}\">\n\t\t<div class=\"row justify-content-center\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"col-12 col-md-12 col-lg-{{imageWidth}} image-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t<img class=\"w-100\" src=\"@PROJECT_PATH@/assets/images/1-4plmvrhagbftlktlw4-xqq.webp\" alt>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t<div class=\"col-12 col-md-12 col-lg\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"text-wrapper align-left\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<h1 class=\"mbr-section-title mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-section-title\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-5\" mbr-if=\"showTitle\"><b>Setting up Landing Zone Project on Google Cloud using pfSense Firewall — Part I/IV</b></h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t<p class=\"mbr-text align-left mbr-fonts-style mb-4\" mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" mbr-if=\"showText\" data-app-selector=\".mbr-text, .mbr-section-btn\">\n\t\t\t\t\tIn this 4 part series of tutorial we’ll be configuring a landing zone project using Hub &amp; Spoke network topology on Google cloud. In the first part (this blog) we’ll do basic configuration of VPCs and pfSense firewall VM on Google cloud.\n\t\t\t\t\t</p>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div mbr-buttons mbr-theme-style=\"display-7\" class=\"mbr-section-btn align-left mt-3\" mbr-if=\"showButtons\" data-toolbar=\"-mbrBtnMove\"><a class=\"btn btn-success-outline\" href=\"https://medium.com/@pateljheel/setting-up-landing-zone-project-on-google-cloud-using-pfsense-firewall-part-i-565f013548b0\" data-app-placeholder=\"Type Text\" target=\"_blank\">Read</a></div>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t</div>\n\t</div>\n</section>",
